**Research Context (Complete):** Defense in Depth employs multiple layers (physical, network, host, application, data) of overlapping security controls across SDLC to mitigate threats. Integrates with NIST SSDF (SP 800-218: PO/PS/PW/RV practices), NIST CSF, OWASP SAMM, CIS Controls. Examples: Auth/authorization (app layer), encryption (data), logging/monitoring (all). No single control; failure of one doesn't compromise all (e.g., SolarWinds: layered response limited damage). NCCIC/ICS-CERT emphasizes DiD for ICS/software (layered controls for resilience).
